  <CalDefinition Description="When triggered, the &#x201c;Add Other Network&#x201d; selection on the Wi-Fi Networks view is greyed out. Pressing the &#x201c;Add Other Network&#x201d; button will show the feature restricted pop-up (see GIS-500). If the user has already started the &#x201c;Add Other Network&#x201d; process and the driving mode lockout is then triggered, the process is cancelled, the feature restricted pop-up (GIS- 500) is shown, and the user is returned to the screen that initiated the &#x201c;Add Other Network&#x201d; process." Name="AddWiFiNetworkDriverWorkload" References="GIS 512 5.5.1.1*MY17 Driver Workload Restriction Items" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
